tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within or very close to normal limits. Hemoglobin A1c and glucose indicate good glycemic control. Slightly elevated chloride is likely not clinically significant in isolation. Renal function (urea, creatinine), electrolytes, and calcium are normal. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected; recommend clinical correlation.
